<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President of Peru</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am glad to receive your telegram in regard to the good effect of
                            Secretary Root’s visit, and trust that not only this pleasing occasion,
                            but all that concerns the intercourse of the two countries may tend to
                            their mutual friendship and esteem.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>